They lady said it’s made in special Turkish bread which sounded good. I requested the meat well done. They took too long to bring food to our table even though they weren’t busy. When they brought the sandwiches they were cold , meat was red inside. No sauce or anything in the sandwiCh , literally bunch of red onions , lettuce and four small pieces of undercooked meat. And the special “bread” turned out to be regular flour tortillas which wasn’t even cooked it was plain white, I guess that’s why the sandwich was cold. We asked the server whether that’s the usual wrap they use as we were told it’s turkish bread, he said he doesn’t know.  I wish I could give less than one star. Save your money and go somewhere else because they don’t care.

I am adding one more comment because I could not add pictures to the prior one.  I bought a lb of baklava from here, full pistachios, and paid as full pistachios.  When I got back home, it was clear that some of the baklavas does not have pistachio in it. The ones with no pistachio called `Durum baklava` and `Dilber baklava` in their website.  As you will see, some varieties have crushed pistachios. Some have ground pistachios, as a paste. But in some,  so clear it is something else.  So, if these varieties do not have pistachio in them, why did you sell them to me as they have? If they do not have pistachio in them, why did you charge me the pistachio price? And whatever you use in them, definitely not walnuts or pistachios, why don't you let people know, so they know what they are paying for?  Don't you know, Our'an says:  Woe to those who give less Who, when they take a measure from people, take in full. But when they have to give by measure or weight to men, give less than due. (83:1-3)
